summary: A speaker questions whether owning one 4.5 million dollar house is a better investment than owning fifteen 500,000 dollar houses. The speaker illustrates the scenario with visual aids of houses and money, explaining that with multiple properties, the absence of one tenant is less impactful due to the presence of others.
transcript: Do you think it would be a better investment to own one 4.5 million dollar house or 15 $500,000 houses? Which would you prefer? I want 15! I mean, you've got one house, you don't have a tenant. You're in a bit of trouble, right? You've got 15 houses, someone moves out, who cares? I've got 14 other tenants. You've got to question the efficiency of your money.
